quran[20]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,16,"And surely We created man and know what his<i class=""s"">(inner) </i>self whispers to him, for We are nearer to him than his jugular vein."
  50,17,"As the two receptors{1}receive<i class=""s"">(him) </i>, one on the right and one on the left, constantly seated.",footnotes:1:Two angels who receive everyone’s words and deeds during his/her life and record them.
  50,18,"Not a word does he utter, but close to him is a watcher, constantly ready."
  50,19,"Then came the daze of death with the truth: “That is what you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>were trying to avoid.”"
  50,20,"And the Trumpet was blown{1}: “That is the Day of the Threat.”",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in past tense, this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  50,21,"And every soul came forward, accompanied by a driver and a witness{1}.",footnotes:1:Two angels: one drives the person to the place of assembly and the other is a witness to all his/her deeds.
  50,22,"“Indeed, you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>were oblivious to this, so We removed your veil and your sight today is<i class=""s"">(as sharp as) </i>iron.”"
  50,23,"And His comrade{1}said, “This is what I have ready with me.”",footnotes:1:According to Ibn ʻAshour, some exegetes said that this comrade is an angel, and others said it is his intimate friend in life, while others said it is his devil which used to whisper to him.
  50,24,"“Cast<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>into Hell, every stubborn relentless denier,"
  50,25,"preventer of good, transgressor, doubter,"
  50,26,"who has set up another deity with Allah. So cast<a class=""sup""><sup>dl </sup></a>him into the severe punishment.”"
  50,27,"His comrade said, “Our Lord, I did not make him exceed all limits, but he was in extreme misguidance.”"
  50,28,"He said, “Do not dispute in My presence, for I have warned you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>in advance. "
  50,29,"The decree from Me cannot be changed, and I am not a tyrant unto the servants.”"
  50,30,"On the day when <span class=""h"">We say<sup foot_note=""81204"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>to Hell, “Are you full?” And it says, “Are there any more?”"
  50,31,"And the Garden<i class=""s"">(of Paradise) </i>was brought closer to those mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>, not far away."
  50,32,"This is what <span class=""h"">you</span><a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><span class=""h"">are promised<sup foot_note=""81205"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>—for every constant preserver who often turns to God,"
  50,33,"the one who inwardly feared the All-Merciful and came with a penitent heart."
  50,34,"“Enter<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>it in peace; that is the Day of Eternity.”"
  50,35,"Therein they have whatever they desire, and We have even more."
